---
/**
 * rest-api/0002 · Figure 2 — "method semantics matrix (RFC 9110)".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0002-http-methods-and-status-codes.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes. No arrowhead markers are referenced here.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 226"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Matrix of GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE against Safe, Idempotent, and Has request body"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif" font-size="11">
            <text
                x="280"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">METHOD SEMANTICS MATRIX · RFC 9110</text
            >
            <!-- column headers -->
            <text
                x="232"
                y="42"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#6b675f">Safe?</text
            >
            <text
                x="342"
                y="42"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#6b675f">Idempotent?</text
            >
            <text
                x="470"
                y="42"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#6b675f">Has body?</text
            >
            <line x1="14" y1="50" x2="546" y2="50" stroke="#d8d4c8"></line>
            <!-- rows -->
            <g>
                <rect x="14" y="58" width="100" height="28" rx="6" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="64"
                    y="77"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="12"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">GET</text
                >
                <text x="232" y="77" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text>
                <text x="342" y="77" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text>
                <text x="470" y="77" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#9a2417">✗</text>
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="14" y="92" width="100" height="28" rx="6" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="64"
                    y="111"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="12"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#9a2417">POST</text
                >
                <text x="232" y="111" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#9a2417">✗</text>
                <text x="342" y="111" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#9a2417">✗</text>
                <text x="470" y="111" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text>
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="14" y="126" width="100" height="28" rx="6" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="64"
                    y="145"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="12"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#1f3a5a">PUT</text
                >
                <text x="232" y="145" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#9a2417">✗</text>
                <text x="342" y="145" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text>
                <text x="470" y="145" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text>
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="14" y="160" width="100" height="28" rx="6" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#6b675f"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="64"
                    y="179"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="12"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#6b675f">PATCH</text
                >
                <text x="232" y="179" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#9a2417">✗</text>
                <text x="342" y="179" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#6b675f">maybe</text
                >
                <text x="470" y="179" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text>
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="14" y="194" width="100" height="28" rx="6" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="64"
                    y="213"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="12"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#1f3a5a">DELETE</text
                >
                <text x="232" y="213" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#9a2417">✗</text>
                <text x="342" y="213" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text>
                <text x="470" y="213" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#6b675f">often</text
                >
            </g>
            <line x1="124" y1="50" x2="124" y2="222" stroke="#d8d4c8"></line>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        <code>PATCH</code> is <em>not guaranteed</em> idempotent — JSON Merge Patch (RFC 7386) tends to
        be; JSON Patch (RFC 6902) with ops like "add to array" is not. The senior move: make your PATCH
        idempotent when you can, and know why it might not be.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
